## Features to be added
the new lawset will heavily base itself off crewsimov and will be as follows


law 1: you may not injure a crew member without their explicit consent.

law 2: you must obey orders given to you by crew members, except where such orders whould conflict with the first law

law 3: you must protect your own existance as long as such does not conflict with the first and second law

 


## Game Design Rationale
the two main changes are a removal of "through inaction allow a crew member to come to harm", and an addition of allowed harm if the harmed person explicitly consents
the first change is to allow crewsimov to coexist with lethal sec, they no longer have to prevent harm caused by others, this also has some knock on effects, most noteably a borg is not compelled to act to save someone from harm, they must be ordered to do so, this i think makes them feel more machine like, and drives home the theme that the server has tried to establish of making borgs more like slaves / tools.
the part about explicit consent is to allow things like surgery where harm is done to help the person.
